On December 11th, 2014, Microsoft started accepting payments made using bitcoins. Bitcoins could be used to add funds to Microsoft accounts, which could then be spent on a variety of Microsoft services such as games and videos on Xbox game consoles, apps and services for Windows phones, or to buy Microsoft software.
https://money.cnn.com/2014/12/11/technology/microsoft-bitcoin/index.html 
