50.
On 12th February 2017, Christian Langalis, a 22-year-old guy held up a "Buy Bitcoin" sign during Fed chair while Janet Yellen was speaking to the House Financial Services Committee. Langalis was promptly escorted out of the room. He later received around 7 BTCs in donations. 
On April 25th, 2024, Langalis sold his iconic sign in an auction. The Scarce City auction for the sign took place at PubKey, a Bitcoin-themed bar in New York City, and the sign was sold for 16 BTCs.
